    <NOTES>Gold-medal 11C target with Fuller's ESB profile bias. Process-critical checkpoints: (1) oxygenate only once at pitch, (2) start fermentation at 64.4F (18C), (3) at start of Day 4 ramp gently rouse yeast once to prevent premature flocculation and support diacetyl cleanup, (4) pass forced VDK (diacetyl) check before crash, (5) package with strict oxygen control. Single-infusion mash target: 151.0F (66.1C) for 60 min, then mash out at 168.0F (75.6C) for 10 min. Water build from RO target: Ca 110, SO4 150, Cl 80, Mg 5, Na 15, HCO3 40 ppm. Suggested salts for total liquor 29 L: gypsum 8.0 g, calcium chloride 4.5 g, epsom 1.0 g; adjust mash pH to 5.30 at room-temp reading. Brew-day control targets: pre-boil volume 6.3-6.8 gal (23.8-25.7 L), pre-boil gravity 1.043-1.046; post-boil volume (pre-chill) 5.2-5.5 gal (19.7-20.8 L), post-boil gravity (pre-chill) 1.055-1.058; track actual boil-off rate. Fermentation schedule: D0-3 at 64.4F (18C), D4-6 at 67.1F (19.5C) with yeast rouse on D4, D7-9 at 68.0F (20C), with forced VDK check on D8-9 and terminal FG stable 48 hr before crash. Add invert sugar with 10 min left in boil. Keep post-boil bitterness smooth; avoid aggressive late hopping. Carbonation target 1.9-2.1 vols; best judging window 3-6 weeks post-package.</NOTES>
    <TASTE_NOTES>Firm but smooth bitterness, rich toffee-biscuit malt, marmalade and floral hop notes, restrained English esters, dry-balanced finish.</TASTE_NOTES>
